-- 
South Korean Companies to Build South African Plants, Business Day Reports

-- B y   G o r d o n   B e l l
-- 
2011-07-08T05:35:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-08/s-korean-companies-to-build-south-african-plants-business-day-reports.html
South Korean companies, including
 Posco (005490) , the steelmaker, HSG Heavy Industries Co. and  LG
Electronics Inc. (066570)  plan to build manufacturing plants in  South
Africa , Business Day reported.  Other companies planning to set up operations were Hankook
Tire Co. and Korea Trade Insurance Corp., the Johannesburg-based
newspaper said.  Africa  offers profitable opportunities for South
Korean companies, it cited Byung-Sam Kim, director-general for
Africa at the Korean Trade and Investment Promotion Agency, as
saying.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Gordon Bell  at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  